olicy issues on a daily basis, the attitudes of colleagues in various political parties, and the tensions created when grassroots and mainstream activism intersect with each other. The only major book to look at gay and lesbian politics in three culturally similar but politically disparate countries, On the Fringe explores the political workings and impact of a modern social movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGay liberation movementzCanada. 0aGay liberation movementzGreat Britain. 0aGay liberation movementzUnited States. 0aGay peoplexPolitical activityzCanada. 0aGay peoplexPolitical activityzGreat Britain. 0aGay peoplexPolitical activityzUnited States. 0aGaysxPolitical activityzCanada. 0aGaysxPolitical activityzGreat Britain. 0aGaysxPolitical activityzUnited States. 4aGay & Lesbian Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSociology & Social Science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172963840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501729638423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501729638/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles